# Cursor Rules — Financial Tracker

## Project Overview

Personal finance tracker: Next.js 16 App Router, TypeScript strict, PostgreSQL 16, Prisma 6, Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui, TanStack Query v5, Zustand.

## Before Writing Code

Always read these files first:
- `GEMINI.md` — Complete build specification
- `DESIGN.md` — Visual design system
- `CLAUDE.md` — Additional coding rules

## Core Architecture

- **Accounting:** Double-entry via transaction rows. Balance always computed, never stored.
- **Income/Expense:** Classified by `Category.type` (INCOME/EXPENSE/TRANSFER_FEE), not by transaction `type`.
- **Transfers:** Two linked rows in `prisma.$transaction()`, shared `transfer_group_id`, excluded from P&L.
- **Soft Delete:** `deleted_at` on all models. Prisma extension auto-filters. Never hard-delete.
- **Auth:** iron-session encrypted cookie, argon2 passwords, single user.

## File Conventions

- Server Components by default. Add `'use client'` only for interactivity.
- Colocate components near their page when used once. Shared → `src/components/shared/`.
- API routes: `src/app/api/[resource]/route.ts` following the standard pattern (auth → Zod → Prisma → respond).
- Service layer: `src/lib/services/[resource].ts` for complex business logic.
- Hooks: `src/hooks/use-[resource].ts` wrapping TanStack Query.
- Stores: `src/stores/[name]-store.ts` using Zustand.
- Types: shared in `src/types/`, feature-specific colocated.

## Code Patterns

```typescript
// API Route pattern (every route)
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  await requireAuth();
  const body = await request.json();
  const data = schema.parse(body);  // Zod before Prisma
  const result = await prisma.model.create({ data });
  return NextResponse.json({ data: result }, { status: 201 });
}

// Component pattern
interface Props { /* typed props */ }
export function ComponentName({ ...props }: Props) { /* ... */ }

// Hook pattern
export function useResource() {
  return useQuery({ queryKey: ['resource'], queryFn: () => fetch('/api/resource').then(r => r.json()) });
}
```

## Formatting

- Currency: `formatIDR(amount)` → `Rp12.500` (no decimals for IDR)
- Dates: `formatDate(date)` → `18 Apr 2026` (Jakarta timezone)
- Short amounts: `formatIDRShort(amount)` → `15.0jt`, `500rb`
- Class names: `cn('base', condition && 'modifier')` from `src/lib/utils.ts`

## What NOT To Do

- Don't add `balance` field to Account model
- Don't install NextAuth, Supabase, Firebase, SQLite
- Don't send raw transactions to LLM (summaries only)
- Don't skip Zod validation
- Don't create single-row transfers
- Don't hard-delete anything
- Don't use `any` type — use `unknown` and narrow

## shadcn/ui

Components installed via `npx shadcn@latest add [component]`. Don't manually copy component code.
Custom components build on top of shadcn primitives.

## Testing

- Unit tests: Vitest for services, validators, utils
- Integration: API route tests with test DB
- E2E: Playwright for critical flows
- A11y: axe-core in Playwright

## Deployment

- Docker on Oracle VPS
- User manages reverse proxy (OpenResty) — don't generate proxy configs
- PostgreSQL in Docker Compose
- Prisma migrations run at deploy time
